Slovenia May Become Entry for China Balkans Investment, STA Says

-- B y   B o r i s   C e r n i
-- 
2011-09-13T14:17:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-13/slovenia-may-become-entry-for-china-balkans-investment-sta-says.html
Slovenia may become a springboard
for  China ’s investment in the Balkans, STA newswire  reported 
citing Chinese deputy Foreign Minister Fu Ying.  “There isn’t a country in the world that has build so much
infrastructure in the last 30 years as China,” Fu Ying was
quoted as saying by the Slovenian newswire. “We have modern
technology and this is what is most needed in the Balkans.”  Fu Ying said Chinese companies are likely to invest into
the chemical, pharmaceutical and the car industry in the region,
according to STA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Boris Cerni in Ljubljana, Slovenia, at 
 bcerni@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  